Your code is correct, it will return "review" if user's score is greater th
than passMark and "pass" otherwise. So no changes needed in your Tundra pro
program. Here is how it looks like (without any comments to maintain the mi
minimalism of your request):

```tundra
val report = {
  user: {
    name: "Ada",
    score: 68
   },
  passMark: 70
};

if(report.user.score > report.passMark) {
  print("review");
} else {
  print("pass");
}
```
